cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper presents a new local descriptor for 3D shapes that is produced by a convolutional network trained on large datasets of 2D images and synthetic dense point correspondences. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories, as it deals with image-based shape analysis and rendering. Additionally, the use of deep learning techniques and large datasets suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of shape-to-scan matching suggests that the paper may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
